    "en": {
      "title": "Instruction of the Secretary of Defense on National Security",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Defense Secretary Retired General Kamal Gunaratne has said that Sri Lanka should act cautiously to face all security threats.",
        "He said this yesterday (17) while speaking at a research seminar conducted after the establishment of the National Defense College. He further informed.",
        "Defense Secretary Kamal Gunaratne said issues including arms and drug trafficking, illegal unregulated fishing, global warming and consequent sea level rise, climate change, increased marine pollution and impact on the marine environment have had a serious impact on Sri Lanka's security in the Indian Ocean. (a)"
      ],
